**The buying recommendation:** For chains under 7mm width at standard lengths, solid construction is preferred — the price premium is manageable and the structural advantage is real. For chains 11mm and above, semi-solid is the practical option — solid construction at 15mm width would make the chain prohibitively expensive and heavy for daily wear.

### **Cuban Link Chains: The Complete Breakdown**

**Cuban links are Blue Nile's most popular men's chain category — and the one with the most critical construction detail (solid vs. semi-solid) to evaluate.**

### **Why Cuban Links Are the Dominant Men's Chain in 2026**

The Miami Cuban link — interlocking oval links with flat, faceted surfaces — has been the defining men's chain style for over a decade. In 2026, Cuban links account for approximately 60% of all men's gold chain purchases online.

The flattened, reflective link surfaces catch light aggressively from multiple angles, the interlocking structure provides excellent security, and the variety of available widths makes Cuban links appropriate across every formality level from casual to luxury.

