## **Rope Chains: Every Option Compared**

**Rope chains are Blue Nile's most diverse style category — available from $635 to $13,090 in multiple metals, widths, and construction types.**

The rope chain features spiral-twisted links creating a helical pattern that mimics twisted rope. Its multiple twisted surfaces catch light from many angles simultaneously — making rope chains inherently reflective even at narrow widths.

The "diamond cut" variation adds machine-cut facets to the twisted links, maximizing light capture further.

### **The Rope Chain Construction Types**

**Standard Rope:** Twisted links without additional faceting. Produces a warm, soft sparkle.

**Diamond-Cut Rope:** Machine-cut facets added to each twisted link — multiplying the light-reflective surfaces. A diamond-cut rope catches dramatically more light than a standard rope of equal width. Note: "diamond cut" refers to the faceting technique, not the gemstone.

**Solid Rope:** Continuous metal throughout — heavier, more durable, more expensive.

**Hollow/Lightweight Rope:** Hollow interior — lighter, less expensive, more susceptible to denting.

### **James Allen Rope Chains (Entry Level — Post-Merger)**

**Ultra-slim 1.6mm rope — White Gold:**

