## **Byzantine Chains: The Most Intricate Structure**

**The Byzantine chain is the most complex chain architecture in Blue Nile's catalog — interlocking rings folded and connected in a multi-dimensional pattern that creates a textured, almost woven appearance.**

Byzantine chains require significantly more manufacturing time per unit length than any other chain style. Each link involves multiple interconnected rings rather than a single solid link.

The resulting texture catches light from many angles simultaneously, producing a rich visual depth no other chain style replicates.

**Important pricing note:** Byzantine chains are priced significantly higher per millimeter of width than simpler styles — because the intricate link construction uses more metal and labor per inch regardless of chain width.

### **Narrow Byzantine — 3.4mm:**

**[24" Men's Byzantine Chain in 14K Yellow Gold (3.4mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/24-mens-byzantine-chain-in-14k-yellow-gold-34-mm-item-195773?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)** — **$10,880**

At 3.4mm, the Byzantine already costs $10,880 — more than a 7mm Cuban ($7,369) because of the complex link construction's material requirements.

### **Wide Byzantine — 6.5mm:**

**[24" Men's Byzantine Chain in 14K Yellow Gold (6.5mm)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/24-mens-byzantine-chain-in-14k-yellow-gold-65-mm-item-150484?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)** — **$38,345**

